{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"040c09f0-fbe1-4000-a893-be6cd7dd309e","content":"Here's what you need to do:\n\n1. **Remove** the `xunit.runner.visualstudio` package reference.\n\n2. **Add** the `xunit.v3.runner.mtp` package (xUnit v3) **or**, if staying on xUnit v2, add `xunit.runner.mtp`:\n   ```xml\n   <!-- For xUnit v2 (your current version): -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.mtp\" Version=\"1.5.0\" />\n   ```\n   ```xml\n   <!-- Or migrate to xUnit v3: -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.v3\" Version=\"1.0.2\" />\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.v3.runner.mtp\" Version=\"1.0.2\" />\n   ```\n\n3. **Enable MTP** in your project file:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n4. **Run tests** with:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   Or run the test project directly (MTP produces an executable):\n   ```bash\n   dotnet run --project YourTests.csproj\n   ```\n\n**Key differences to expect:**\n- MTP makes your test project a standalone executable (no separate test host process).\n- `dotnet test` still works but uses the new platform under the hood.\n- Some VSTest-specific `.runsettings` options may need updating.\n\nWould you like help modifying your actual `.csproj` file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"88806ca5-814f-4ce8-a7fb-2d744428b4c2","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration path.","outputTokens":454},"id":"039ca621-485b-4aa3-a0b5-a1587a775938","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:43:17.373Z","parentId":"a83284fd-dc52-47b7-8725-541ff062764a"}
